Description: Pre-owned Fender American Deluxe Stratocaster I bought this guitar used about 2 years ago. Rare Montego Black color which is a black base with gold metal flake in it. Matching gold pickguard and rear cavity cover. Fender Samarium Cobalt Noiseless single coil pickups in the neck and middle position and a Fender Atomic Humbucker in the bridge.This guitar has the S-1 Switching System in it which lets you get all kinds of different tones and pickup combinations. Guitar plays great with nice low action with room to go lower with the neck adjustment plate.Has the pop-in tremolo arm. Cosmetically the neck is perfect, no major dings or chips. The body I would say is 7 out of 10. No major scratches but there are some fine scratches by the input jack and there are numerous little indentions in the clear lacquer around the top contour of the body and some on the back. I'm not sure where these came from as they were on it when I bought it. And about three small dings through the paint that have been touched up. Doesn't effect the playability of this guitar and it's gotten plenty of compliments while I've had it. I've tried to picture these as best I can. On the whole the finish still shines and has a deep sheen to it. I would say the frets are at 80%.They are polished like diamonds and don't have flat spots or fret out anywhere on the neck. Only notable fret wear are the 1st, 11th, and 12th frets. Guitar will ship in molded SKB Fender Hard case with TSA locks and two keys.
Title: Fender American Deluxe Stratocaster HSS Montego Black Electric Guitar
